\backslash
begin{cor}
\backslash
label{cor}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $f:X\to Y$
\end_inset

 be a continuous map of topological spaces.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\subseteq X$
\end_inset

 is an irreducible subspace, its image 
\begin_inset Formula $f(Z)$
\end_inset

 is irreducible.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{cor}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 If 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{2}$
\end_inset

 are non-empty open subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $f(Z)$
\end_inset

, their preimages in 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 have a non-empty intersection.
 This shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{1}\cap U_{2}\neq\emptyset$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{lemma}
\backslash
label{lemma1.17}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 be a topological space.
 A subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\subseteq X$
\end_inset

 is irreducible if and only if its closure 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{Y}$
\end_inset

 is irreducible.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{lemma}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 A subset 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is irreducible if and only if for any two open subsets 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\cap U\neq\emptyset$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\cap V\neq\emptyset$
\end_inset

 we have 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\cap(U\cap V)\neq\emptyset$
\end_inset

.
 This implies the lemma because an open subset meets 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 if and only if it meets 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{Y}$
\end_inset

.
 Indeed, one direction is trivial.
 For the other direction, we prove the contrapositive: 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap Y=\emptyset$
\end_inset

 implies 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap\overline{Y}=\emptyset$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap Y=\emptyset$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $X\backslash U$
\end_inset

 is a closed subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 which contains 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore, 
\begin_inset Formula $X\backslash U$
\end_inset

 must contain 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{Y}$
\end_inset

, as 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{Y}$
\end_inset

 is the smallest closed subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 which contains 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

.
 This implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap\overline{Y}=\emptyset$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 is and open subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and if 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is an irreducible closed subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

, then 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\cap U$
\end_inset

 is open in 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 and hence an irreducible closed subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 whose closure in 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

.
 Together with 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Lemma~(
\backslash
ref{lemma1.17})
\end_layout

\end_inset

, this shows that there are mutually inverse bijective maps
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
\{Y\subseteq U\mid Y\text{ is irreducible and closed}\} & \leftrightarrow & \{Z\subseteq X\mid Z\text{ is irreducible and closed with }Z\cap U\neq\emptyset\}\end{array}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\mapsto\overline{Y}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\mapsto Z\cap U$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{defn}
\backslash
label{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 A maximal irreducible subset of a topological space 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is called an 
\series bold
irreducible component 
\series default
of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{defn}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Let 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 be a topological space.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

Lemma~(
\backslash
ref{lemma1.17})
\end_layout

\end_inset

 shows that every irreducible component is closed.
 The set of irreducible subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is ordered inductively, as for every chain of irreducible subsets their
 union is again irreducible.
 Thus Zorn's lemma implies that every irreducible subset is contained in
 an irreducible component of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

.
 In particular, every point of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is contained in an irreducible component.
 This shows that 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is the union of its irreducible components.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Irreducible Affine Algebraic Sets
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{prop}
\backslash
label{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\subseteq\mathbb{A}^{n}(k)$
\end_inset

 be a closed subset.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is irreducible if and only if 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)$
\end_inset

 is a prime ideal.
 In particular 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}^{n}(k)$
\end_inset

 is irreducible.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{prop}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)$
\end_inset

 is a prime ideal and suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $Z=Z_{1}\cup Z_{2}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{1},Z_{2}$
\end_inset

 are closed subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)=I(Z_{1})\cap I(Z_{2})$
\end_inset

 and since 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)$
\end_inset

 is prime, we must either have 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)\supset I(Z_{1})$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)\supset I(Z_{2})$
\end_inset

.
 Without loss of generality, assume 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)\supset I(Z_{1})$
\end_inset

.
 Now we apply 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 to both sides to get 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\subset Z_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is irreducible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Conversely, suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is irreducible and suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $fg\in I(Z)$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\langle fg\rangle\subset I(Z)$
\end_inset

, and after applying 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 to both sides, we obtain 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
V\langle fg\rangle=V(f)\cup V(g)\supset Z.
\]

\end_inset

Since 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is irreducible, either 
\begin_inset Formula $V(f)\supset Z$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $V(g)\supset Z$
\end_inset

.
 Without loss of generality, say 
\begin_inset Formula $V(f)\supset Z$
\end_inset

.
 Applying 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

 to both sides, we obtain 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\in I(V(f))\subset I(Z),
\]

\end_inset

so 
\begin_inset Formula $I(Z)$
\end_inset

 is prime.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


